Losing project folders can feel catastrophiclets get them back for you. Heres a structured recovery roadmap:

Immediate Steps Dont Write Over That Space

  1. Stop using the drive where the files were storedevery bit written may overwrite recoverable data. citeturn0search5turn0search6
  2. Check the Recycle Bin (on Windows) or Trash (on macOS/Linux). If the folders are there, right-click and restore. citeturn0search12

Restore from Backup (If Enabled)

  • Windows File History / Previous Versions: Rightclick the parent folder or drive where the folder was stored, select Restore previous versions. Choose a version from before deletion and restore it. citeturn0search0turn0search7
  • Mac Time Machine / other OS backups: Use your backup tool to travel back to when the folders were present (if applicable).

Use Data Recovery Software

If no backup or Recycle Bin option is available:

Tool Folder Structure Recovery Highlights
Recuva (Piriform) Yes Lightweight, portable wizard, deep scan; supports NTFS/exFAT/FAT citeturn0search11turn0search22
EaseUS Data Recovery Wizard Yes 2GB of free recovery, preserves structure; preview before restore citeturn0search10turn0news25
PhotoRec / TestDisk No structure in PhotoRec; TestDisk may recover full partitions citeturn0search24turn0search26
DMDE Yes (up to 4,000 files in freeware) Good for complex recoveries; some UI limitations citeturn0search23
Disk Drill Yes Free up to 2GB, deep and quick scan modes citeturn0search27
Acronis, Macrium Yes (via imaging) Great for future prevention; requires preuse setup citeturn0news21turn0search28

Next Steps:

  1. Install and run the recovery tool from a different drive, not the one with lost files citeturn0search3turn0search6.
  2. Deep-scan the affected drive for lost folders and files.
  3. Restore to a new location on another drive to avoid overwriting.

If Working in an IDE (e.g. code, video editing software)

Some development tools maintain local history or autosave snapshots:

  • Eclipse: Right-click src, use Restore from Local History citeturn0search4
  • Premiere Pro: Check your Auto-Save backup folder or dynamic link for older project versions citeturn0search2
  • Others (IntelliJ, VSCode, etc.) may have similar local history features.

Recommended Recovery Flow

  1. Recycle Bin/Trash restore fast and simple.
  2. Backup restore check File History or Time Machine.
  3. Scan with recovery tool start with Recuva or EaseUS for Windows.
  4. IDE-specific local history check your app's backup folder.
  5. If successful, copy recovered folders to a safe location and resume your endpoint sync.
